The paper presents a deep learning approach for joint compression and classification of EEG and EMG signals. The use of deep autoencoder architecture and multimodal data representation suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the sub-categories of machine learning (cs.LG), neural and evolutionary computing (cs.NE), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), computer vision and pattern recognition (cs.CV), and social and information networks (cs.SI).
